Tidymodels example: Hotels

xCIT

04 May, 2021

Introduction

This is a template project for the data science in R project class.

All of the code, data and images are taken from the tidymodels website.

The Question

How accurately can we predict which hotel stays included children and/or babies based on a set of features (e.g., the cost of the stay)?

The Data

hotels
set.seed(123)
splits      <- initial_split(hotels, strata = children)

hotel_other <- training(splits)
hotel_test  <- testing(splits)

set.seed(234)
val_set <- validation_split(hotel_other, 
                            strata = children, 
                            prop = 0.80)

The Model

lr_plot <- 
  lr_res %>% 
  collect_metrics() %>% 
  plot_auc_by_penalty()
lr_plot

Top 5 models:

top_models <-
  lr_res %>% 
  show_best("roc_auc", n = 5) %>% 
  arrange(penalty) 
top_models
lr_best <- 
  lr_res %>% 
  collect_metrics() %>% 
  arrange(penalty) %>% 
  slice(12)

lr_auc <- 
  lr_res %>% 
  collect_predictions(parameters = lr_best) %>% 
  roc_curve(children, .pred_children) %>% 
  mutate(model = "Logistic Regression")

autoplot(lr_auc)

The Answer

Using penalized logistic regression we achieve a prediction accuracy (quantified as the ROC AUC) of 0.88.
